NAME
listen_sock - Set a TCP stream socket to listen.
SYNOPSIS
#include <libswoccommon.h>

int listen_sock(int *sockfd, int *portno);
DESCRIPTION
The listen_sock function effectively performs a listen with error handling.
PARAMETERS
sockfd - a pointer to the socket.

portno - a pointer to the port number to be used with the socket.
RETURN VALUE
mge_errno is returned.
.br
0 on success.
.br
Non-zero Failure
ERRORS
mge_errno is set as required.
